I was doing some multithreading on the particlesystem, the code can be found [here](https://gist.github.com/lukaspj/448c8910951ad6f4c232#file-particlethreading-cpp-L3-L11).

But I encountered an issue when there were several threads running, adding some debug info, I got this in the console:

```
Created queue
Finished a Particle Worker Thread
Finished a Particle Worker Thread
Finished a Particle Worker Thread
Finished a Particle Worker Thread
Deleting queue
Deleted queue
Created queue
Finished a Particle Worker Thread
Finished a Particle Worker Thread
Finished a Particle Worker Thread
Deleting queue
First-chance exception at 0x10E818EC (Empty_DEBUG DLL.dll) in Empty_DEBUG.exe: 0xC0000005: Access violation reading location 0xFEEEFEF6.
Deleted queue
```

As you can see, in the last pass, it deletes the queue before all the threads have finished, afaik `pool->flushWorkItems();` should ensure that all the threads have finished.

This is the main code that triggers this issue:

``` c++
   OutputDebugStringA("Created queue\n");
   ParticleQueue* queue = new ParticleQueue(mParticlePool->GetParticleHead()->next);
   ThreadPool* pool = &ThreadPool::GLOBAL();

   F32 t = F32(ms) / 1000.0;

   for (U32 i = 0; i < 4; ++i)
   {
      ThreadSafeRef< ParticleUpdateItem > item(new ParticleUpdateItem(queue, t, this, BHVs));
      pool->queueWorkItem(item);
   }

   pool->flushWorkItems();

   OutputDebugStringA("Deleting queue\n");
   delete queue;
   OutputDebugStringA("Deleted queue\n");
```

